                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/192</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Penfield</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1129. See Department’s instruction 707, January 8. Emphasize the fact Frank L.
                    Ghiloni born American citizen, was impressed into Italian army and was serving
                    against his wishes. Earnestly request his release and permission return this
                    country. His mother seriously ill because of his plight. Report result
                    intercession, also Ghiloni’s condition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
